<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>
Essential Presentation library has support for creating slide transition effects in PowerPoint presentation.
</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to add different transition effect for slides.</Paragraph>
<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<Paragraph>The below transition effects are supported as equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint:</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Subtle</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Exciting</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Dynamic Content</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph>The below transition options are supported as equivalent to Microsoft PowerPoint:</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Effect options</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Advance On Time</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Advance Mouse On Click</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Transition Duration</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
